description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Trainee Biomedical Scientist (Band 5 Annex U) / &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a full time (37.5 hours per week) permanent trainee Biomedical Scientist or HCPC registered Biomedical Scientist (Band 5) to join a friendly professional team within the Immunology Department as part of the South of Tyne and Wear Clinical Pathology Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Gateshead site is a state of the art laboratory with all staff rotating into this area to train in specialized techniques and processes. The purpose of the post is to ensure that the Immunology department is able to meet the needs of the service both now and in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be eligible to apply for the post you must meet &lt;strong&gt;ALL&lt;/strong&gt; the essential criteria requirements of the relevant personal specification. Please ensure you respond to all personal specification requirements in your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary offered will be dependent on current progress and previous experience within the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The department will fund any training requirements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be on Gateshead Health NHS Trust terms and conditions of employment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please Contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stephen Nixon on 0191 445 3298&lt;/p&gt;
